00:03:49.000 --> 00:03:55.000
Awesome. Okay. One question we saw come in during the demo was,

00:03:55.000 --> 00:04:01.000
what suggestions do you have for developing a Cordo dashboard over a Shiny app?

00:04:02.000 --> 00:04:08.000
Great question. I think it is kind of a balance of the simplicity of what you're looking for,

00:04:08.000 --> 00:04:14.000
what you hope that your audience can see and do, and then also the resources that you have available

00:04:14.000 --> 00:04:18.000
for actually publishing and sharing your content.

00:04:18.000 --> 00:04:23.000
I would say there's definitely a spectrum of very, very simple kind of quick prototypes

00:04:23.000 --> 00:04:29.000
all the way up to very complex, robust, scalable, interactive apps.

00:04:30.000 --> 00:04:36.000
Cordo dashboards definitely can hit on that kind of like, if you need something quick and simple,

00:04:36.000 --> 00:04:41.000
and Shiny apps can become, again, more complex depending on your needs.

00:04:41.000 --> 00:04:48.000
One nice thing about Cordo dashboards is that you can add interactivity with Shiny.

00:04:48.000 --> 00:04:53.000
So if you're kind of looking for that middle ground of not doing a full-blown Shiny app,

00:04:53.000 --> 00:04:58.000
but you also need toggles and filtering and things like that,

00:04:58.000 --> 00:05:04.000
Cordo dashboards are still an option for you.

00:05:04.000 --> 00:05:06.000
Thank you.

00:05:06.000 --> 00:05:12.000
Yeah, I would just add that, you know, there's sort of this definite like deliberate consideration

00:05:12.000 --> 00:05:17.000
on both the Cordo and Shiny team side that it should be easy for you to move, right?

00:05:17.000 --> 00:05:20.000
If you start in a Cordo dashboard with your prototype,

00:05:20.000 --> 00:05:23.000
it's relatively simple to then add in some Shiny components.

00:05:23.000 --> 00:05:28.000
